ENGINE SPECIFICATIONS:

HANDCRAFTED AMG 4.0L V8 BITURBO ENGINE | 577HP @6,000RPM | 627LB-FT @ 2,500-3,500RPM | COMPRESSION RATIO OF 8.6:1 | DIECAST ALLOY BLOCK & ALLOY HEADS

The 2021 Mercedes-AMG G63 comes with a twin-turbocharged 4.0-liter V-8 engine that produces 577 horsepower and 627 lb-ft of torque. A nine-speed automatic transmission with AMG Steering wheel with paddle shifters. Low-range gearing (2.93:1 reduction) is the standard as are three locking differentials, allowing the G63 to scale steep dirt grades with ridiculous ease. Zero to 60 mph comes in at just 3.9 seconds. Along with its extra power, the G63 has AMG-specific suspension tuning which makes this SUV capable of overcoming any challenge. Properly equipped, the G63 can tow up to 6500 pounds. This G63 comes in G Manufaktur Platinum Black Metallic Exterior and the Interior is in a Classic Red/Black leather with red top stitching.

Taller drivers and passengers will find plenty of headroom and legroom in both the front and rear seats. With the rear seats up, you'll have 38 cubic feet of cargo space. Folding them down (60/40 split) provides nearly 69 cubic feet of cargo space.

The 2021 G63 has crisp 12.0-inch infotainment interface in the front with Android Auto and Apple CarPlay integration as well as navigation. With this infotainment you will be able to control almost every feature of the car. There are two USB ports up front and an SD card reader.

ENGINE SPECIFICATIONS:

HANDCRAFTED AMG 4.0L V8 BITURBO ENGINE | 577HP @6,000RPM | 627LB-FT @ 2,500-3,500RPM | COMPRESSION RATIO OF 8.6:1 | DIECAST ALLOY BLOCK & ALLOY HEADS.

The 2021 Mercedes-AMG G63 comes with a twin-turbocharged 4.0-liter V-8 engine that produces 577 horsepower and 627 lb-ft of torque. A nine-speed automatic transmission with AMG Steering wheel with paddle shifters. Low-range gearing (2.93:1 reduction) is the standard as are three locking differentials, allowing the G63 to scale steep dirt grades with ridiculous ease. Zero to 60 mph comes in at just 3.9 seconds. Along with its extra power, the G63 has AMG-specific suspension tuning which makes this SUV capable of overcoming any challenge. Properly equipped, the G63 can tow up to 6500 pounds. This G63 comes in G Manufaktur Olive Metallic Exterior and the Interior is in a G Manufaktur Saddle Brown/Black leather interior.

Taller drivers and passengers will find plenty of headroom and legroom in both the front and rear seats. With the rear seats up, you'll have 38 cubic feet of cargo space. Folding them down (60/40 split) provides nearly 69 cubic feet of cargo space.

The 2021 G63 has crisp 12.0-inch infotainment interface in the front with Android Auto and Apple CarPlay integration as well as navigation. With this infotainment you will be able to control almost every feature of the car. There are two USB ports up front and an SD card reader.
